<br>
As long as they are not asked to tank mobs that really require defensive disc, they make very good back-up tanks.<br>
<br>
They have a ton of spells and skills that are very usefull, not the least of which are: root, stun, rez, LoH, cure(s), removing curses, some good buffs, and on and on.<br>
<br>
At one point VI gave 'em a skill to silence mobs, but that trivialized so many encounters they had to take it away.<br>
<br>
If I could pick a single thing a paly should get to make them even better end game, I would suggest a defensive disc that is either a smaller percentage then the warriors dmg reduction or lasts for a shorter duration.<br>
<br>
I agree in that I feel for mages, but they still get their moments. When a very difficult mob has wiped all your tanks but is still at a few percent health and the order goes out, &quot;Feed it pets&quot; - those epic mage pets are meaty. Leveling with mages was always a blast as their pet dmg added to some very effecient rain spells made them the masters of sustained dmg. <br>
<br>
Perfect pet control would be a great boon for mages. I would also like to see them get a mana sieve.<br>
<br>
Of course, the end game has given melee classes ungodly good ratio weapns which to balance VI will give casters stronger spells and then create tougher mobs. . .ahhh power creep. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/unazarpazar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazar Pazar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/10/02 2:48:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2285.topic&index=79>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: blah blah</span><hr size=1> /agree Zamtin 100%<br>
